presents the risk stratification commonly used in studies [28,46,84,85]. About 81 % are mild cases, 14 % are severe, and 5 % are critical [28]. Mortality for mild, severe, and critical cases are 98 %, 52 %, and 6 % [84,85]. Severe cases have an unpredictable prognosis solely based on clinical presentation. Laboratory markers including LDH, high-sensitivity CRP, and lymphocyte count estimate the prognosis for these cases (Fig. 3
) [85].
